values:
ahhhhhh, i own high speed internet connection. comcast has high speed internet at $14.99 for three months. so that is what i own. this is the first time i've typed something on a computer not relating to nextel and it's affiliates. because that is all i do now - answer calls from irate nextel customers taking their frustrations out on a little guamanian. i moved out...7 months ago. i live with my ever loving boyfriend james, and keenan - a hip-hop revolutionizer. we are never all home at the same time, so it's almost like i live alone.

my work hours: 4am - 12:30 pm
james' work hours: 9pm to 5:30am
keenan's work hours: 11:30am to 8pm

if you look close enough you will notice that when someone gets off work, another one starts work...we're like a relay race.

i got stoned last night with james, daryl, and andrew. like tooo stoned. i couldn't function. i could barely stand up and i couldn't focus on anything. i thought i was gonna die. i've never felt that way before ever. ew, i hated it.
i got this done today. i'm excited to not be sitting on that tattoo chair anymore today.
i don't remeber taking this pic, but i found it on my computer just now.
i'm an old fart. i'm 24 today.....

i miss the feeling of knowing someone is gonna be there for me no matter what.

it's been a couple years now.

karma's a bitch.

i love fruity pebbles. they're the bombest. i bought some the other day at target. i bought some concealer too, you know, make-up stuff. but that was not the bombest. it didn't match my skin color and they wouldn't take it back. hella gay.

i'm sick again. i must be allergic to whiskey.
new hair-cut. i have bangs now. picking up wes tomorrow night at the airoporto. too bad i work early the next day =(

i couldn't keep my job as a stocker, but oh well. hopefully the h-tizzle will give me more hours. i haven't talked to wes for like, two days =( he went to florida to visit some friends. it's out in the sticks so i don't think he's getting any service on his cell phone. we're gonna need to spend some quality time together when he gets back, cause he'll only be in town for a week before he leaves for three months =( he asked me to make him a business card. i was pretty proud of it cause i haven't done any design since i stopped working at the PDN. i'm sick my room's a mess my car is not running well payday is so far away i miss wes...
sometimes we lie to ourselves to feel happy....

i'm about pretty bored right now. it's so hot. it's 10pm and its still soo hot. does anyone out there have photoshop CS?? i have a question for you if you do. i have a $65 parking ticket and a $91 speeding ticket. donations to me would be greatly appreciated. oh, and a late return on a blockbuster video. oh shit, i know what i'm gonna do...i'm gonna put together the clothes i wanna sell to the buffalo exchange in seattle. it's this cool ass thrift store. i hope to get a reasonable amount of store credit for what i wanna sell to them. then, i can have some hella cool ass used apparel at department store prices. heh, oh well. so here's a picture of me. alkaline trio necklace. it's the only thing i got from the warped tour, and i loooooooooooooooooooooove it.
i'll be in seattle for weekend events. anyone else???? there'll be fireworks!, and me!!!!!

hey you. yeah you with the stick. come here and beat me atop the head with it. go on.
DOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO IIIIIIIIITTTTTTTTTTT!!!!!!!!!! BEEEEAEAAAAATTTTT MEEEEEEEEE!!!!!!!

no picking up jesse no applying at starbucks in seattle no hanging out with wes in seattle yes shopping at value village yes working a 3 hour shift today my plans fizzled out as my day started, oh well. really wanted to go down to seattle today, but like half an hour before i was gonna catch the ferry, my manager calls me to come in at 7. that would of left me with exactly 1 hour of hanging out time in seattle, so poo. if only i didn't like money so much. got a couple tee shirts at the value village and a friggin cool stripped polo and a cool brown button up shirt. looks boy scout-ish, but it isn't. so i guess that made up for not doing anything i planned to do. give me loves people, loves... this isn't the boy scout shirt i was talking about. this was me before i went shopping...
i'm old. i'm gonna settle down soon. hopefully with some hot guy that's in a band. jk, wow, that would be hard, all that touring and practicing. shit, now i gotta start all over again.
went to the casino tonight. lost $25 playing black jack and poker. it was fun, but i think i'll stick with strip poker from now on.

yeah, i'm tired. we had inventory tonight at work. was counting like crazzzzy. thought it would be a lot more fun. i didn't know that a crap load of old-ass-low-income people from some sort of agency were gonna come in with their scanning/counting machines. i'm gonna be dreaming of "beep. beep. beep. beep, SKU CHECK!!!" all night. oh, and i hate how it's so warm in the store. it's friggin washington, FUCKING MAKE IT COLDER!!!!!. i hate the hot. i feel like sticky, sweaty puke when it's hot. that's why i HAD to get away from the island. stina brought me macadamia nuts from hawaii and i got all giddy cause it reminded me sooo much of guam. then she started talking about how she's been going to her chamorro friend's parties. lumpia and babui, i miss the fiesta's sooo much. 

i need to take another photo for my driver's license. it sucks butt. i look like crizzap cause i had just woke up. my parents asked me to go with them to the store and we ended up going to the dmv after. i didn't think i was gonna pass anyway. so i didn't really care about what i looked like. you still wanna try using my driver's license jeanie???????
